GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Grub: Can mutate into various Xayid units.

GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Scorpalisk: Armored melee attacker.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Scour: Reveals a small area. Lasts for a duration of <d ref="Effect,ScourCP,ExpireDelay" precision="1"/> seconds.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Does not detect.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SelectBuilderKeiron: Selects the unit constructing this structure.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SelectWasp: Can mutate into various Xayid flyers.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SelectWorms: Can mutate into various Xayid ground units.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SelfFixProtocol: Heals <d ref="(Abil,VirtusSelffixProtocol,CastOutroTime[0]+0.0125)*Effect,VirtusSelffixProtocol,RechargeVitalRate"/> health over <d ref="Abil,VirtusSelffixProtocol,CastOutroTime[0]"/> seconds while disabling movement and weapons. Reduces received weapon damage by <d ref="-(Behavior,VirtusSelffixProtocolBuff,DamageResponse.ModifyFraction-1)*100"/>%.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/ShockCharge: Consumes energy after it is placed, and when it deals damage. Self-destructs when its energy reserves are consumed.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Siphoner: Formed over a Vespene Geyser to allow harvesting of vespene gas.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SiphonerRich: Formed over a Vespene Geyser to allow harvesting of vespene gas.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SonicImage: Places a sonic image, which the Echo can teleport back to if it remains close by.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SpeedCloak: Cloaks, and increases movement speed by 40% for <d ref="Behavior,SpeedCloak,Duration" precision="1"/> seconds.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Spitfire: Skirmish unit.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SpitfireMadcapRounds: Increased attack range and attack speed for <c val="FFFF80">Spitfires</c>.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Spitter: Long ranged beast that spits acid at enemies, dealing damage in an area. Can issue attacks to specific points on the ground<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SpitterVolatile: The Spitter deals <d ref="Effect,SpitterVolatileBurstDamage,Amount"/> damage in an area around itself when it dies.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/StagnatingBile: Lobs bile at a point, stunning units in it's impact area for <d ref="Behavior,StagnatingBileStun,Duration"/> seconds.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/StaticDBurrow: Buries the structure underground. While burrowed, the structure is unable to attack, and cannot be seen without detection.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/StaticDUnburrow: Unburies the structure, allowing it to resume a normal state.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Stratus: Anti-air defensive structure. <n/><n/><c val="ffff8a">Can attack air units.</c><n/><c val="FFE303">Detector</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Subjecter: Ranged anti-air support unit.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can target ground and air units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SunkenWarren: Contains upgrades for the Kraken and the Raptor.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Enables:</c><n/>- Krakens from the Avian Nest
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Supplimentation: Improves nearby owned production spawn rate by 7%. <c val="FFFF80">Can stack up to 3 times.</c> Also passively heals up to 3 nearby units if they are under 75% health.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SystemOffload: Boosts the attack speed of friendly units by 15% in the target area. Offloads additional performance heavy tasks to the Processing Core, allowing the affected units to run more efficiently.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/SystemRecharge: Transfers energy directly to the target unit.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/TechVault: Contains weapon upgrades for Genetron heavy ground units, and weapon and armor upgrades for Genetron air units.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Enables:</c><n/>- Aquilas at the Manufacturer<n/>- Virtus at the Fabricator<n/>- Badgers at the Assembly Array
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Tesla: Area control specialist. Can construct and launch specialized charges.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Titan: Heavy assault walker.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/ToggleDetector: When active, this unit is a detector, allowing it to see cloaked and burrowed units, while draining energy.<n/><n/><c val="f078ff">Drains <d ref="-1*Behavior,PDDetector,Modification.VitalRegenArray[Energy]" precision="1"/> energy per second.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Torrent: Anti-air artillary.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground and air units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Umbra: Tactical cloaking anti-armored specialist. Can be upgraded to use Stealth Compulsion.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UmbraCloakingSystems: Maintains cloaking except after attacking. Weapon damage is increased while cloaked. Re-cloaks after <d ref="Weapon,ShadowCannon,PreEffectBehavior.Duration"/> seconds of not attacking.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UmbraDamageReduction: Damage taken by the Umbra from all sources is reduced by 25% while moving.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UmbraShieldCompulsion: Immediately re-cloaks the unit at the cost of <d ref="Abil,UmbraShieldCompulsion,Cost[0].Vital[Life]"/> of its life.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Unfuse: Releases the Fuse inhabiting this unit, losing the associated bonus.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UnloadAllFerrion: Unloads all units currently loaded into the Ferrion's hold.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeAircraftPlating: Upgrades the armor of Genetron air units.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeAircraftPlatingLev: Further upgrades the armor of Genetron air units.
Maximizes the armor of Genetron air units.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeAircraftWeapons: Upgrades the damage of aircraft weapons.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeAircraftWeaponsLev: Further upgrades the damage of aircraft weapons.
Maximizes the damage of aircraft weapons.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeGroundPlating: Upgrades the armor of all Genetron ground units.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeGroundPlatingLevel: Further upgrades the armor of all Genetron ground units.
Maximizes the armor of all Genetron ground units.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeHeavyWeapons: Upgrades the damage of units produced from the <c val="FFFF80">Fabricator</c>.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeHeavyWeaponsLevel2: Further upgrades the damage of units produced from the <c val="FFFF80">Fabricator</c>.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeHeavyWeaponsLevel3: Maximizes the damage of units produced from the <c val="FFFF80">Fabricator</c>.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeLightWeapons: Upgrades the damage of units produced from the <c val="FFFF80">Manufacturer</c>.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeLightWeaponsLevel2: Further upgrades the damage of units produced from the <c val="FFFF80">Manufacturer</c>.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UpgradeLightWeaponsLevel3: Maximizes the damage of units produced from the <c val="FFFF80">Manufacturer</c>.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Uploader: Key tech structure. Can link to a production facility to increase it's production speed, and unlock tech. Contains research for units that come from the linked structure.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/UploaderInstallationUpgra: Owning at least one <c val="FFFF80">Outfitting Station</c> reduces the preparation time of <c val="FFFF80">Uploaders</c> by 100%.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/VengeanceMissile: Fires a missile dealing 60 (+<d ref="Effect,VengeanceMissileLMImpact,AttributeBonus[Massive]"/> vs Massive) damage to the target.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/VenomousInjection: The <c val="FFFF80">Scorpalisk</c> injects venom when it attacks non-massive units, slowing them by 40%. Lasts for a duration of <d ref="Behavior,VenomInjection,Duration"/> seconds.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Virtus: Heavy tank. Weapons and movement disabled and gains armor after taking critical damage.<n/><n/><c val="f078ff">Energy user.</c><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/VolatileDischarge: After a charge up of <d ref="Behavior,VolatileDischargeAB,Duration" precision="0"/> seconds, the <c val="FFFF80">Volatile Discharge</c> will explode for 200 damage in a large area. If destroyed before charge up is complete, the detonation will be cancelled.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Damages air and ground units, including friendlies.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Volt: Light ranged warrior.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground and air units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Wasp: Can mutate into various Xayid flyers.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Worm: Can mutate into various Xayid ground units.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/XayidCocoon: Xayid units morph in the safety of these cocoons.
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/XayidDen: Creates larva, which are in turn used to mutate various basic creatures.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Enables:</c><n/>- Xayidlings<n/>- Roamers<n/>- Bile Pit from Scavengers
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Xayidling: Mid-ranged fighter.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground and air units</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Xayidling2: Mid-ranged fighter.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Can attack ground units</c><n/><c val="FFFF80">Must be upgraded to attack air units.</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Xayithoan: Aerial detector and spell caster. Can use Adaptive Injection and Protective cloud.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF00">Detector</c>
GameStrings.Button/Tooltip/Zenith: Highly advanced tech facility.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Enables:</c><n/>  - Paragons from the Citadel
GameStrings.DocInfo/DescLong: Adds three additional playable custom made races: Genetron, Keiron, and Xayid.<n/><n/>Basic AI is supported.
